# Catalog ↔ Collection boundary

## Catalog (`lib/features/catalog/`)

- Read-only universe: brands, IPs, series, figures
- Models use **`imageKey`** (opaque); resolve with **`CatalogImageResolver`**
- Runtime: **`CatalogBundleCache`** → **`catalogBundleProvider`** — Firestore one-shot `.get()` via `loadFirestoreCatalogBundle()`; persisted `catalog_bundle_v1.json` for offline; `CatalogBundleMemoryOrigin` (`bootstrapPlaceholder` → `persisted` | `firestore` | `resolved`). **No** APK-bundled metadata JSON.
- UI: **`catalogAvailabilityProvider`** for loading/offline/refresh UX — widgets do not call Firestore for catalog
- Same flat schema only — no nested catalog collections, no `imagePath` on Firestore docs
- Firebase Storage = `catalog/series/<imageKey>.<ext>` and `catalog/figures/<imageKey>.<ext>` only — no URLs or `imagePath` on Firestore docs
- **Search V2:** `CatalogSearchService` + `lib/core/search/` (normalization, token AND, combined haystack) — see [`docs/SEARCH_ARCHITECTURE.md`](../../docs/SEARCH_ARCHITECTURE.md)
- Clone onto shelf only through `catalogTemplateFromSeedSeries` + `CollectionNotifier`
- New catalog-derived providers must `ref.watch(catalogBundleProvider)` (or transitively)

## Collection (`lib/features/collection/`)

- **Source of truth:** `CollectionSnapshot` on disk (codec v2)
- **`ShelfFigure`:** `localImageUri` (user photos), `imageUrl` (catalog asset path / URL) — **never `imageKey`**
- **`ShelfSeries`:** `customCoverImageUri` for user series cover only
- Display priority: `ShelfFigureMedia` (local → cover → imageUrl → placeholder)
- Do not persist Firestore payloads or catalog `imageKey` on shelf rows

## Naming trap

- `features/catalog/models/CatalogSeries` ≠ `collection_domain.CatalogSeries` (shelf template)
- `CollectionCatalog` in `collection/data/` is a **legacy hardcoded** suggestion list — separate from Firestore catalog

## Do not

- Upload private shelf images to Firebase Storage in MVP tasks
- Add Firestore listeners or collection cloud sync without explicit scope
- Mix catalog search DTOs into `CollectionSnapshotCodec`
